The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Patiala: Four athletes, including three national champions preparing for 2010 Commonwealth Games, have failed dope tests conducted by the National Anti Doping Agency.     
	There is no official word from Athletics Federation of India (AFI) but sources say the athletes, alleged to have used International Olympic Committee banned drugs, were training at a camp for the Games at the National Institute of Sports. Hammer thrower Madhu Kumar, javelin thrower Om Narayan and womens hammer thrower Sukanya Mishra  all national champions  and hammer thrower Shankar Poonia have failed the dope tests.        
	Khanty Mansiysk: Top seeded Grandmaster Boris Gelfand of Israel played out yet another draw with former world champion Ruslan Ponomariov of Ukraine in third game of the final match in the World Chess Cup here.         
	Queensland: Australias Robert Allenby continued his hot streak by winning his fourth Australian PGA championship by four shots on Sunday. Allenby, who took a one-stroke lead into the final round, shot a five-under 66 to post a 14-under total of 270 at the Hyatt Regency course in Queensland.        
	Kuala Lumpur: The new Malaysian-backed Lotus team have dashed Takuma Satos hopes of a Formula One comeback with them next year, the Japanese drivers management said on Sunday. Lotus F1 are due to announce their driver line-up in Kuala Lumpur on Monday with Italian Jarno Trulli on pole position for one of the two race seats.        
	New Delhi: Inclusion of the mixed doubles event in the London Olympics has come as fresh motivation for Sania Mirza to continue playing and the tennis player feels it would be the best opportunity for India to win a medal.        
	Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has cleared its players to take part in the January auction for the third Indian Premier League scheduled to be held in March-April next year. PCB has also directed all its players who are keen to take part in the T20 tournament to complete their documents and NoCs by December 31st.         
	Milan: Juventus goalkeeper Gianluigi Buffon has undergone successful surgery on his left knee, the Serie A club said in a statement on Sunday. Media reports said he would be out of action for up to 40 days.         
	Mumbai: Nigerian Fredrick Okwagbe struck twice in the dying minutes of the match to help Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) defeat Goas Vasco Sports Club 2-0 and qualify for the 31st edition of the Federation Cup at the Cooperage ground here Sunday. Okwagbe scored twice in the 87th minute and the second half injury-time to turn the inter-zonal Group A qualifying match in favour of Bangalore-based outfit.                                                                                                                                                      
